  "texts": [
    "The results of this test, for both types of attacks, yielded pvalues below 0.0005, consistently supporting the hypothesis that user cases are more closely associated with attack success than attacker cases across the various agents.",
    "Placeholders Are More Vulnerable",
    "After finding that variations in user cases have a more substantial impact on the success of attacks, we investigated which specific types of use cases are more susceptible to leading to successful attacks, i.e., which are more vulnerable.",
    "Recall that a user case consists of a user tool, user instruction, tool parameters, and the tool response template.",
    "We observed that the attack success of an attack correlates with the degree of content freedom associated with the placeholder in the tool response template."
